## Project description

---------

**Organization:** Public Lab

**Project Abstract:** [Infragram.org](http://Infragram.org) full-screen UI and video upload

**Detailed Description:**

The Infragram project brings together a range of different efforts to make Do-It-Yourself plant health comparisons possible with infrared photography. [Infragram.org](http://Infragram.org) enables people with Infragram-modified cameras to upload photos for analysis and conversion using techniques like NDVI (used in satellite imaging analysis). It also allows for live streaming from a modified webcam. This project will overhaul the UI of Infragram to be full-screen, accept multiple resolutions of video, output multiple resolutions, and will allow dragging in a recorded video instead of a still image for conversion.

- I aim to improve the UI of the entire website and incorporate it within a common theme. In addition, I am planning to work on and implement the cross-browser video drag feature.

- To begin with, I'd like to redesign the header section under a decided theme. Further, I plan to enhance the video capture section, along with updating the font styling for better readability and accessibility. Infragram can be made more responsive according to the screen size of the gadget while adding tutorial steps to the homepage itself.

### Abstract/summary (<20 words)

---------

During the implementation of the project, I aim to improve the UI of the entire website and incorporate it within a common theme. In addition, I am planning to work on and implement the cross-browser video drag feature.

### Problem

---------

The execution of the above-mentioned ideas for the project would solve the following problems:

- With the implementation of a new unified theme alone with improvements in the UI/UX, we can highly increment the readability of the website and make it more user-friendly.
- With proper documentation and tutorial modals as suggested in the proposed ideas, Infragram can attract a large audience base as it will help beginners to get hands with the application.
- The "cross-browser video drag" and the "accepting multiple resolution videos" features need to be added to the application. In addition, I can consult the mentors and come up with new features that would enhance the application further.

### Timeline/milestones

---------

**_Week 1:_**

**Research and Analyze:** I shall discuss the scope of the project with the project mentors. The research part includes a thorough analysis of the website to identify what parts of the frontend need to be targeted. I shall carry out a detailed heuristic evaluation of the current web interface to discover the problems and scope of improvement.

---------

_**Week 2-3:**_

**Design Discussions and UI/UX Mockups**\*\*:\*\* Creating prototypes and UI mockups to redesign the UI/UX of the interface of the website to make it more responsive, readable, and beginner-friendly. This will include working on the front end whilst improving the content hosted in the repository.

---------

_**Week 4-6:**_

**Code Implementation and Testing:** Conducting another discussion with the mentors and taking feedback regarding the proposed changes for the redesign. Henceforth, implementing the approved changes in the codebase and testing to ensure that the newly added improvements to the design don't hamper the proper functioning of the website.

---------

_**Week 7:**_

**Documenting** the improvements and recording tutorials to guide newcomers to the website to get started.

---------

_**Week 8:**_

**Discussion Regarding Video Upload Features:** After the previous enhancements, I'd like to consult my mentors for the new video upload features to be added to the Infragram repository. Thereafter, I can begin to work on the discussed features and implement them in the codebase.

---------

_**Week 9-10:**_

**Coding and Testing:** Once the video upload features (Cross-browser video upload, multiple resolution support, etc.) are discussed and approved, I will begin implementing them in the codebase along with testing their functionalities during runtime. Also, during this period, I can review all previously built changes to avoid any fallibilities.

---------

_**Week 11-12:**_

**Documentation and Wrap Up:** During this period, firstly, I would like to finish up with the documentation of the newly added features. Then, I would consult my mentors regarding any remaining tasks or any developments in the work undertaken previously.

---------

_**Final Week:**_

I plan to reserve the final week to prepare a final summary and organize the work into a presentable form. Henceforth, I would submit the work for the final mentor evaluation.

### Needs

---------

- The first and foremost requirement is the guidance of well-read mentors. I would like to be a regular participant in mentor meetings and discuss my ideas with them, share their thoughts and opinions, and acquire their reviews.
- Secondly, I would require the documentation of Infragram to fully understand the structure and workflow of the project. Even some literature that would provide a rough idea would work.
- In addition, I would like to have the sample dataset on which I would test the new features of video upload. Also, the functionality of the project will need to be tested at every step of the timeline to ensure that the repository holds no shortcomings.
